Net Interest Income
Net interest  income decreased $426 million to $42.9 billion in
2021 compared to 2020. Net interest yield on a fully taxable-
equivalent (FTE) basis decreased 24 basis points (bps) to 1.66
percent for 2021. The decrease in net interest income was
primarily driven by lower interest rates and average loan
balances, partially offset by higher average balances of debt
securities. For more information on net interest yield and the FTE
basis, see Supplementa l Financial Data on page 31, and for
more information on interest rate risk management, see Interest
Rate Risk Management for the Banking Book on page 79.(1)
