The provision for credit losses improved $15.9 billion to a benefit
of $4.6 billion in 2021  compared to 2020. The benefit was
primarily due to improvements in the macroeconomic outlook and
credit qualit y. For more information on the provision for credit
losses, see Allowance for Credit Losses on page 73.Noninterest Expense
